A duplicate of #1654 with additional commits that automatically address incorrect style, created by [Restyled][]. Since the original Pull Request was opened as a fork in a contributor's repository, we are unable to create a Pull Request branching from it with only the style fixes. The following Restylers [made fixes](https://restyled.io/gh/TokTok/repos/c-toxcore/jobs/1327519): - astyle - clang-format To incorporate these changes, you can either: 1. Merge this Pull Request *instead of* the original, or 1. Ask your contributor to locally incorporate these commits and push them to the original Pull Request
Expand for example instructions ```console git remote add upstream https://github.com/TokTok/c-toxcore.git git fetch upstream pull//head git merge --ff-only FETCH_HEAD git push ```
**NOTE**: As work continues on the original Pull Request, this process will re-run and update (force-push) this Pull Request with updated style fixes as necessary. If the style is fixed manually at any point (i.e. this process finds no fixes to make), this Pull Request will be closed automatically. Sorry if this was unexpected. To disable it, see our [documentation][]. commit.message: Fix tcp relay test: add jfreegman test node.
Enable testnet on travis and circle.
Make onion announce code work with vanilla nacl
Use test network in autotools build.
Add some missing cleanup functions in new_messenger
Format fixes and remove a bunch of unnecessary debug prints
Add missing null pointer check
Never send null data in groupchat lossless UDP
Clean up and improve group define/function names
Also exclude imported sodium sources.
Make sure data is not null before re-sending a group message ack

Move structs back into the .c files, making them private.

Added accessors where needed.
Replace all error `fprintf`s with `LOGGER_ERROR`.
Fix some group connection issues

Fix a bug preventing non-founders from rebooting a dead group from save

Sanctions are not saved to the tox save file, so when a peer tried to re-create
a dead group, others were not able to sync with them due to the inability
to validate the sanctions credentials. Now in such a situation we simply
don't send sanctions until a moderator or founder arrives.

Add autotest for group moderation

Fixed a couple issues in the other group tests as well
Fix a bug in the group lossless implementation
Add lossless message testing to group message test

Revert regression

create_array_entry() needs to be able to handle empty received handshake ack packets

Improve ability to establish direct UDP connections in groups

We now occasionally send our own IP info to a peer in a ping packet if we don't have a direct
connection established already. This fixes an issue where if two peers handshake via a
TCP connection, they would never be able to establish a direct connection.
Don't call memcpy on sanctions list if it's empty

Remove a bunch of redundant calls to ipport_isset() and pack_ip_port()

These functions only need to be called once before the loop

style: Make group code compliant with the latest tokstyle.

We no longer allow multiple declarators per declaration.
Improve groupchat logging

Don't allow peers to send LAN addresses in ping packets

Some code clean up as well

Fix ipport_self_copy()

This function would sometimes return a close node's IP address instead of our own.
Fix a couple group handshake issues

Refactor group pings

We now have independent ping timers for each peer and re-try failed pings immediately

More small fixes

- Remove unused variable announced_node
- Fix bug causing self_join callback to be triggered when it shouldn't be
- Some renames and cleanup

Refactor peer syncing

We now send each peer in a single packet instead of the entire
peer list in one big packet. This removes a theoretical hard
limit on the number of peers that can join a group and ensures
that the maximum packet size doesn't exceed the MTU of common
network media.

Some unnecessary syncing logic was removed. This will increase
the aggressiveness of syncing with more redundancy, but should
improve overall syncing speed.

Additionally, the ping packet now contains a checksum of the
public key hash of all confirmed peers instead of just the peer
count. This will ensure that sync requests will be made in
the case that all group peers have the same peer count, but a
different set of peers (i.e. group splits).

Finally - an unused 32-bit uint was removed from the sync request
packet.
Remove code that wasn't doing anything

Use flags to tell peers what info we want in a sync response.

Previously a sync response was very wasteful in that all group
info was sent to the peer making the request, including info
that they didn't need

Attempt to fix a group handshake bug

Also removed some unnecessary calls to set_peers_checksum() (already called in peer_add())
Lots of groupchat code cleanup

Add packet request throttling

This is to prevent packet request spam when we receive many out of order packets at once
Fix bug causing topic callback to sometimes give client the wrong peer id

A better way to get unique peer ID's

Also revert a small bug introduced in the last commit
More code cleanup
Try to limit unnecessary sync request spam
Lower some group list limits to account for the new max packet size

Add sanctions list entry purging

When the list is full it will attempt to remove an entry for an offline peer.
If all sanctioned peers are online an error will be returned and the situation
can be dealt with manually by the caller

Make save format moderator list a fixed size

This allows us to change the max number of moderators without breaking
the save format. This should be a temporary fix.

Refactor peer deletion

We now flag peers that should be deleted and handle the event from the main loop.
In addition we now have exit types which are passed to clients via the API

Fix handling sync errors and reconnections

TCP connections need to be severed before we attempt to re-add a
peer, and peers need to be deleted if they give us incorrect
sync info

Put gcc_check_received_array() in main loop to remove possible recursion

Also add some extra checks to make sure we can't send/recv packets from
peers that are pending deletion
Fix a few more group handshake bugs
Remove unnecessary 4 byte field from handshake packet
Fix bug sometimes preventing handshakes from taking place

Make group TCP relay connections more robust

We now periodically check that we're connected to at least one TCP relay, and
if not, we attempt to add relays. Previously we never checked our
connections with relays if the group state was connected
Make sure clients get peer exit event
Make group announcements work without TCP requirement
Fix bug causing invalid TCP nodes to be copied to group announcements
Fix bug preventing tcp relays from being saved

Improve error handling when we add TCP relays

Also revert last commit
Fix group exit type enum style: Foo_Bar -> FOO_BAR
More groupchat code cleanup

Refactor invite sending and main do_gc loop

Instead of spamming peers for invites for 15 seconds straight in intervals we now
have a simple timer and make one request per n seconds.

In addition, the CS_MANUALLY_DISCONNECTED and CS_FAILED states were merged
with CS_DISCONNECTED and state logic was simplified.

Improve self group announcement mechanism

Self announcements are now refreshed when either our TCP or UDP connection changes
as long as one or the other is connected. We no longer spam the DHT needlessly
when our TCP status updates. In addition, we always attempt to refresh
our announcements every 10 minutes if possible.
Fix a bug preventing tcp connections from being initiated with initial peer

Kill tcp connection when peer is marked for deletion

This fixes an issue where a tcp connection number was being killed twice which
would occasionally cause buggy behaviour if a new peer was assigned that same
id (e.g. on a rejoin or reconnect)
Fix rejoin spam on handshake and remove unused function

Add peer count back into ping packet

This greatly reduces the amount of unnecessary sync requests

Reduce unnecessary amount of group announcement spam

Instead of every peer refreshing their announcements every n minutes we ask
each peer to play a lottery every n minutes where their chance of winning
is relative to the number of peers in the group, and announce only if they
win. We only need a bare minimum of one announcement in the DHT at any given
time, so this ensures that while not constantly burdening the DHT with
unnecessary traffic.

A couple small fixes

- Make sure peers can't be marked for deletion twice
- Ignore handshake packets from peers we've already handshaked with
Reset self announce timer even if we don't announce

Simplify and improve group handshake protocol

- We no longer have the peer who receives a sync request send the requestor's
  info to the rest of the group as this was redundant (and broken)

- Lots of unnecessary/duplicate code pertaining to handshaking was removed

- Message ID's are set to a fixed number when we send/receive handshake
  packets instead of incrementing. This is because it's impossible to
  proceed with the connection if either of those first two packets
  are lost, so incrementing the counters just messes up the order

- Sync responses no longer contain the number of peers being sent
  in the series of peer announces as this was unnecessary
Broadcast a quit packet before we rejoin a group
Some fixes and improvements to group autotests

Self-announce/self-connection refactor

- Remove a TCP callback that wasn't doing what it was supposed to be doing
- We now update our UDP and TCP connection status from the main loop
- Properly keep track of our TCP connection status: previously we were
  updating our announcement every time we connected to an individual
  peer via TCP, now we update it when we add or remove a TCP relay

  unnecessary)
